**Code Explanation:**

The code performs a wavelet-based multiscale analysis of the 2D turbulence velocity field. It uses the PyWavelets library with the db4 wavelet basis and periodic boundary conditions to decompose velocity snapshots into detail coefficients. For each scale j in {1, ..., 6}, it computes the wavelet energy E_j(x, y, t) and estimates the eddy lifetime T_eddy(j) via the temporal autocorrelation of this energy. Tracers are re-advected in filtered velocity fields u_j (reconstructed by zeroing coefficients below scale j) using RK4 integration. Finally, it computes Levy flight parameters (alpha, gamma, nu) for each scale and tests the CTRW prediction alpha = 1 + beta/(2-beta) where beta proportional to T_eddy^delta. The mcculloch_alpha function estimates alpha using the McCulloch quantile method. The run_wavelet_analysis function performs the decomposition, energy calculation, tracer advection, and parameter fitting.

