The code performs a wavelet-based multiscale analysis of the 2D turbulence velocity field. It uses the PyWavelets library with the db4 wavelet basis and periodic boundary conditions to decompose velocity snapshots into detail coefficients. For each scale j in {1, ..., 6}, it computes the wavelet energy E_j(t) as a time series (array) for each scale j, allowing for the calculation of the temporal autocorrelation C_E(tau, j). Tracers are re-advected in filtered velocity fields u_j (reconstructed by zeroing coefficients below scale j) using RK4 integration. Finally, it computes Levy flight parameters (alpha, gamma, nu) for each scale and tests the CTRW prediction alpha = 1 + beta/(2-beta) where beta proportional to T_eddy^delta. The mcculloch_alpha function estimates alpha using the McCulloch quantile method. The run_wavelet_analysis function performs the decomposition, energy calculation, tracer advection, and parameter fitting.

**Modifications:**

Corrected the energy calculation to produce a time series of energy values for each scale j instead of a scalar. Ensured that energy is an array of shape (n_snaps,) before computing the autocorrelation. Maintained the use of db4 wavelets and periodization mode for periodic boundary conditions.

