The error occurred because `dE_dt` (derived from the full energy spectrum time series) and `dAlpha_dt` (derived from the windowed analysis) have vastly different lengths. The causal analysis requires aligning these time series. I have modified the code to interpolate `dE_dt` onto the time points corresponding to the window centers used in the non-stationarity analysis, ensuring that the arrays passed to `np.corrcoef` have identical lengths.

